OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1773778273
OL,3,CMan accused of Natalie McNally's
OL,4,Cmurder will not take the stand
OL,6,FIn the exchanges, both described being
OL,7,Fin love and excited about the
OL,8,Fpregnancy.
OL,10,FNatalie McNally told Mr McCullagh she
OL,11,Fwas "addicted to him", she "loved him"
OL,12,Fand he "made her happy" in the months
OL,13,Fbefore her murder.
OL,15,FA Detective Chief Inspector told the
OL,16,Fjury he was not in a position to say
OL,17,Fif it was a loving relationship based
OL,18,Fon the messages.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/6
